{
  "doc_id": "17377",
  "text": "Generally, controlled trials are rare for paraproteinaemic neuropathies, which makes it difficult to recommend any particular evidence-based immunotherapy [CITATION_1] (Table 4 ). In a randomized double-blind placebo-controlled crossover trial IVIg was not effective in the majority of 11 patients with IgM paraproteinemic demyelinating neuropathy [CITATION_2] . Another double-blind crossover trial of 22 patients with IgM paraproteinemic demyelinating neuropathy demonstrated a clinical benefit at 4 weeks [CITATION_3] . These results indicate that IVIg may only have a short-term benefit in the treatment of IgM paraproteinemic neuropathy [CITATION_4] ].",
